explanation: This solution uses a sliding window approach with two pointers (left and right) to traverse the string s. It maintains a count of characters in the string t and updates the count as the window moves. When the window contains all characters of t, it tries to minimize the window by moving the left pointer. The time complexity is O(m + n) as it visits each character in s and t once. The space complexity is O(n) for storing the count of characters in t.

